Mesquite Merchant Men’s League

Mesquite Chiropractic continues to hold onto first place but we had two teams record the best bowling of the night. Smith Financial Group won 16 points paced by Carl Larsen 242, 204 – 616 and Edward Hoepfner 204 from C.I.T.Y. Shoppes who won 4 points. Foot and Ankle also won 16 points with Ken Thompson 203 and Bob Monson Jr 200 against Bank of Nevada who took the other 4 points.

Mesquite Lock Doc won 15 points led by Carl Roth 268 – 644 and James Hartley 212 from Colonial Management who won the other 5 points. Mesquite Chiropractic our league leader won 14 points with hot bowling by Steve Ginther 237, Danny Barker 233, Jan Kusy 226 and Terry King 225, 202. A Valley Engineers won 6 points with Chuck Gibson high game of 204. Falcon Ridge Dental won 14 points with good bowling from Gary Magnuson 228, Tom Huff 226 and Don Smalley 206. Simplot Silica Sand took the other 6 points with Dallas Archibald 231.

Beaver Dam Station won 13 points from Mesquite Elks Lodge won the other 7 points with about average bowling from both teams. Eureka Casino Resort won 11.5 points high game by Maury Hardman from Oasis Chiropractic Center who won 8.5 points.

Mitchell Farmer Insurance won 11 points paced by Max Burgess 224 and Doug Love’s 203 from Intermountain Golf Cars who won 9 points high game by Brian Collins 215. Mesa View Quick Care won 11 points with David Duffy 226 from H & R Bock winning the other 9 points led by Darwin Wimer 237, 227. Freelancers also won 11 points with good team bowling from Master Villas Resort taking the other 9 points with Gary Moore 246 – 615, Jeff Jacobson 246 and Rick Jones 202.
